HEADWORD: Tuberculin
<hw>Tu*ber"cu*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tubercle</er>.]</ety> <def>A fluid containing the products formed by
the growth of the tubercle bacillus in a suitable culture
medium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

